membership:
Ensure general coordination, monitoring and supervision of the national Eurodesks, in particular with regard to tasks related to the European Youth Portal and providing relevant feedback to the Commission (DG EAC and EACEA); 
Be the main contact for the Commission (DG EAC and EACEA) on behalf of the network of national Eurodesks; 
Support the development and implementation of quality control procedures for the Eurodesk network, including the development of quality indicators, the quality catalogue and the European Youth Portal Editorial Guidelines; 
Deliver training courses and information sessions to the national Eurodesks on the European Youth Portal, European Youth Strategy and the Erasmus+ programme, along with other European Union initiatives as advised by DG EAC;  
Provide information to the national Eurodesks concerning key EU events, as well as facilitating the sharing of best practice for national activities related to these events; 
Promote Eurodesk information services at the European level; 
 Provide appropriate information services and advice to European-level organisations or bodies offering information to young people regarding European opportunities for young people, in particular with regard to funding opportunities under EU programmes;  
Contribute to European level high visibility activities, such as promoting the EU Youth Strategy and the Erasmus+ programme, along with other European Union initiatives as advised by DG EAC
